#: chaotic_pfc.comms.channel:2 of
msgid "channel.py"
msgstr ""

#: chaotic_pfc.comms.channel:3 of
msgid ""
"Transmission-channel models sitting between the chaotic transmitter and "
"the receiver."
msgstr ""

#: chaotic_pfc.comms.channel:6 of
msgid "Eight channels are provided:"
msgstr ""

#: chaotic_pfc.comms.channel:8 of
msgid ""
":func:`ideal_channel` — noiseless pass-through used to establish a best-"
"case baseline for chaos synchronisation."
msgstr ""

#: chaotic_pfc.comms.channel:10 of
msgid ""
":func:`fir_channel` — a symmetric FIR low-pass filter built on top of "
":func:`scipy.signal.firwin`, representing a band-limited physical link."
msgstr ""

#: chaotic_pfc.comms.channel:13 of
msgid ":func:`awgn` — additive white Gaussian noise."
msgstr ""

#: chaotic_pfc.comms.channel:14 of
msgid ":func:`channel_impulsive` — AWGN with Middleton Class-A impulsive noise."
msgstr ""

#: chaotic_pfc.comms.channel:15 of
msgid ""
":func:`channel_multipath` — multipath channel with configurable tap "
"delays and gains."
msgstr ""

#: chaotic_pfc.comms.channel:17 of
msgid ""
":func:`channel_interferers` — composite channel (AWGN + DCSK interferer +"
" narrow-band WiFi-like interferer), lives in "
":mod:`chaotic_pfc.comms.dcsk`."
msgstr ""

#: chaotic_pfc.comms.channel:19 of
msgid ""
":func:`channel_urban` — combined urban channel with impulsive noise, "
"multipath, and interferers, lives in :mod:`chaotic_pfc.comms.dcsk`."
msgstr ""

#: chaotic_pfc.comms.channel:22 of
msgid ""
"All accept the transmitted signal ``s`` as a 1-D array and return the "
"received signal ``r`` of the same length. The FIR channel additionally "
"returns its filter coefficients so they can be overlaid on the PSD plots "
"produced by :mod:`chaotic_pfc.plotting`."
msgstr ""

