#: chaotic_pfc.comms.channel.fir_channel:3 of
msgid ""
"The channel is built with :func:`scipy.signal.firwin` using "
"``pass_zero=True`` (true low-pass) and unit sampling frequency "
"normalisation (``fs=2.0``). The DC gain of the resulting filter is "
"normalised to ``1.0``."
msgstr ""

#: chaotic_pfc.comms.channel.fir_channel:9 of
msgid ""
"Normalised cutoff frequency ``ω_c / π ∈ (0, 1)``. Defaults to ``0.99`` — "
"i.e. the channel passes almost everything, mimicking a very lightly band-"
"limited link."
msgstr ""

#: chaotic_pfc.comms.channel.fir_channel:12 of
msgid "Length of the FIR filter in samples. Must be a positive integer."
msgstr ""

#: chaotic_pfc.comms.channel.fir_channel:13 of
msgid ""
"Window function passed through to ``firwin``. Any name accepted by "
":func:`scipy.signal.get_window` is valid — common choices are "
"``\"hamming\"``, ``\"hann\"``, ``\"blackman\"``."
msgstr ""

#: chaotic_pfc.comms.channel.fir_channel:17 of
msgid ""
"* **r** (*ndarray, shape (N,)*) -- Received signal, ``s`` filtered "
"through the FIR coefficients. * **h** (*ndarray, shape (num_taps,)*) -- "
"Filter coefficients, useful for overlaying the channel response   on PSD "
"plots. * **Implements** (:class:`~chaotic_pfc.comms.protocols.Channel`.)"
msgstr ""

#: chaotic_pfc.comms.channel.fir_channel:17 of
msgid ""
"**r** (*ndarray, shape (N,)*) -- Received signal, ``s`` filtered through "
"the FIR coefficients."
msgstr ""

#: chaotic_pfc.comms.channel.fir_channel:18 of
msgid ""
"**h** (*ndarray, shape (num_taps,)*) -- Filter coefficients, useful for "
"overlaying the channel response on PSD plots."
msgstr ""

